  "text": "Stated differently, a decrease in pH i through mitosis may act as a master clock controlling microtubule disassembly/assembly probability ratios by altering the electrostatic interactions of tubulin dimers. This, in turn, would determine the timing and dynamics of postattachment chromosome motions through metaphase [CITATION_1] .",
